{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":27,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":1,"text":"Job continued his discourse, saying:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":2,"text":"As God lives, who has deprived me of justice, and the Almighty who has made me bitter,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":3,"text":"as long as my breath is still in me and the breath from God remains in my nostrils,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":4,"text":"my lips will not speak unjustly, and my tongue will not utter deceit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":5,"text":"I will never affirm that you are right. I will maintain my integrity until I die.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":6,"text":"I will cling to my righteousness and never let it go. My conscience will not accuse me as long as I live!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":7,"text":"May my enemy be like the wicked and my opponent like the unjust.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":8,"text":"For what hope does the godless person have when he is cut off, when God takes away his life?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":9,"text":"Will God hear his cry when distress comes on him?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":10,"text":"Will he delight in the Almighty? Will he call on God at all times?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":11,"text":"I will teach you about God’s power. I will not conceal what the Almighty has planned.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":12,"text":"All of you have seen this for yourselves, why do you keep up this empty talk?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":13,"text":"This is a wicked man’s lot from God, the inheritance the ruthless receive from the Almighty.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":14,"text":"Even if his children increase, they are destined for the sword; his descendants will never have enough food.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":15,"text":"Those who survive him will be buried by the plague, yet their widows will not weep for them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":16,"text":"Though he piles up silver like dust and heaps up fine clothing like clay —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":17,"text":"he may heap it up, but the righteous will wear it, and the innocent will divide up his silver.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":18,"text":"The house he built is like a moth’s cocoon or a shelter set up by a watchman.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":19,"text":"He lies down wealthy, but will do so no more; when he opens his eyes, it is gone.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":20,"text":"Terrors overtake him like a flood; a storm wind sweeps him away at night.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":21,"text":"An east wind picks him up, and he is gone; it carries him away from his place.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":22,"text":"It blasts at him without mercy, while he flees desperately from its force.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:27:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":27,"verse":23,"text":"It claps its hands at him and scoffs at him from its place."